 :tx/rationale "CRITICAL INSIGHT from prompt-optimization + API-as-prompt: Task titles ARE activation prompts. The current design puts 500+ chars in :task/title including BACKGROUND, APPROACH, ACCEPTANCE — but braid task list truncates to ~80 chars. This means agents see TRUNCATED ACTIVATION PATTERNS. TASK-DECOMPOSE extracts BACKGROUND/ACCEPTANCE into separate datoms (:task/background, :task/acceptance), but the TITLE still contains all the text. The fix: task titles should be SHORT activation patterns (e.g., 'TOPO-DENSITY: Coupling density matrix rho_C and coordination entropy S(rho_C) (INV-TOPOLOGY-005, INV-COHERENCE-001)') — 80-120 chars max. The BACKGROUND is in :task/background. The ACCEPTANCE is in :task/acceptance. Display shows short title in list, full context in show. This is PROGRESSIVE DISCLOSURE applied to task management."
